     <int-org-section id="SAARC.IO.149" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
          <heading>Organization</heading>
          <heading-note>April 2024</heading-note>
          <int-org-section id="SAARC.IO.150" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Summit Meeting</heading>
               <p>Heads of state and of government of member states represent the body's highest authority. The 18th summit meeting, the last to take place, was held in Kathmandu, Nepal, in November 2014. The 19th regular summit, initially scheduled to be convened in November 2016, in Islamabad, Pakistan, was postponed indefinitely.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="SAARC.IO.151" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Council of Ministers</heading>
               <p>The Council comprises the ministers responsible for foreign affairs of member countries, who normally meet each year in September. The Council may also convene in extraordinary session at the request of member states. The responsibilities of the Council include formulation of policies, assessing progress, confirming new areas of co-operation, and appointing the Secretary-General.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="SAARC.IO.152" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Standing Committee</heading>
               <p>The Committee has overall responsibility for the monitoring and co-ordination of programmes and financing, and determines priorities, mobilizes resources and identifies areas of co-operation. It meets at least once a year. The Committee is supported by a Programming Committee composed of senior officials.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="SAARC.IO.153" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Technical Committees</heading>
               <p id="SAARC.IO.130">SAARC's six Technical Committees cover Agri­culture and Rural Development; Environment; Health and Population Activities; Science and Technology; Transport; and Women, Youth and Children. They are responsible for forming, co-ordinating, implementing and monitoring programmes in their respective areas of focus. Each committee comprises representatives of member states and meets annually.</p>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="SAARC.IO.154" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Secretariat</heading>
               <p id="SAARC.IO.131">The secretariat comprises the Secretary-General and eight Directors, from each member country, responsible for the following working divisions: Agriculture, Rural Development and the SAARC Development Fund; Economic, Trade and Finance; Education, Security and Culture; Energy, Transport, Science and Technology; Environment, Natural Disasters and Biotechnology; Human Resources Development and Tourism; Information and Poverty Alleviation; and Social Affairs.</p>
               <p>In March 2023 member governments agreed on a nominee from Bangladesh to assume the role of Secretary-General. The appointment had been due to be made by Afghanistan on the basis of alphabetical rotation, however its Taliban-led administration is not recognized by any SAARC member state.</p>
