          <int-org-section id="IO-SAARC.10" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Regional Centres</heading>
               <!--~..&nat. foc. pts-->
               <p usage="ewyb edio">Regional Centres established in member states support the SAARC secretariat in promoting co-operation in the following areas: agriculture (based in Dhaka, Bangladesh); culture (Colombo, Sri Lanka); disaster management (Gujarat, India); energy (Islamabad, Pakistan); and tuberculosis and HIV/AIDS (Kathmandu, Nepal). The foundation documents for a proposed South Asian Regional Intelligence and Co-ordination Centre on Transnational Organized Crime, to be based in Colombo, were approved in April 2018 by senior officials from Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Maldives, Nepal and Sri Lanka.</p>
               <p id="SAARC.IO.137" usage="sasia">Regional Centres established in member states support the SAARC secretariat in promoting regional co-operation. Each Centre is managed by a Governing Board comprising representatives from all the member states, the SAARC Secretary-General, and the ministry responsible for foreign affairs of its host government.</p>
